  "original_title": "\u0b85\u0bb5\u0bc1\u0bb8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bcb\u0bb2\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bbe \u0b9a\u0bc6\u0bb2\u0bcd\u0bb2 \u0bae\u0bc1\u0baf\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0bb1 77 \u0baa\u0bc7\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0b95\u0bc8\u0ba4\u0bc1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "77 people who tried to go to Australia were arrested",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "77 people were arrested early today (11) for illegally traveling by motor boat from Kaluwangeni beach, Batticaloa to Australia.",
        "17 people, including a woman, have been handed over to the Ebravur police and the other 60 have been taken to the Trincomalee naval camp by boat, the police said.",
        "According to the information received by the Naval Intelligence Unit, at 2 o'clock in the morning today, the boats of the Navy surrounded the engine boat that was traveling in the sea area of \u200b\u200bthe Batticaloa Ebravoor Police Division.",
        "In this, 60 anti-immigrants were arrested and 77 people were arrested by the Naval Intelligence Unit along with the police, including 17 people who were waiting in a van at Kaluwangeni beach to board the said illegal boat. (a)"
      ],
